LIBRARY COMPROMISE
President Glenn suggest announced his promised Feb. 1 de-
vision on library closing hours early Thursday evening In a letter
to faculty and students, suggest indicated that the Library would
remain open until 12 midnight on all nights except Saturday.
During ﬁnfl papers and examinations, however, the library
WIII remain open until at least 1:00 A.M, or later.
who decision represents l compromise between the demands
oi many students that the library stay open until 1:00 AM. and
the recommendation or the Faculty Library Committee that the
library maintain its present 11:15 PM, closing time.
Closing hours for all classroom buildings (except party Gym-
valium) — now 11:00 P.Mi — will in revised depending on cost
and availability of BM} spain
The letter also stated that Forum and North Campus Inungl
closing hours would remain the same, and that South Campus
younger Will remain open until twelve midnight subject to th!
consent of the individual hall.
